      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "#92684 fix(doctor): skip empty parent groupAllowFrom warning when all accounts override",
        "body": "\"## Summary\\n\\n`openclaw doctor` warns about an empty top-level `groupAllowFrom` even when every child account has its own populated effective group allowlist. The runtime resolves `account ?? parent`, so the parent's empty list is never read \\u2014 the warning is a false positive.\\n\\n**Root cause:** `scanEmptyAllowlistPolicyWarnings()` checks the parent channel config independently of its child accounts. When the parent's `groupPolicy` is `\\\"allowlist\\\"` but `groupAllowFrom` is empty, it warns \\u2014 without checking whether every account under it already supplies its own list.\\n\\n**Fix:** Before emitting the parent-level group-allowlist warning, check whether **all** child accounts have their own populated effective group sender allowlist:\\n- Explicit `groupAllowFrom` always counts\\n- For fallback-capable channels (`groupAllowFromFallbackToAllowFrom=true`), account-level `allowFrom` also serves as the effective group allowlist\\n- Disabled accounts are excluded from the check (they are inactive)\\nIf all enabled accounts override, skip the parent warning. DM-policy warnings at the parent scope are preserved.\\n\\n## Real behavior proof\\n\\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** `openclaw doctor` false-positive warning when top-level `groupAllowFrom` is empty but every account overrides it with its own populated list (either via `groupAllowFrom` or `allowFrom` with fallback).\\n\\n**Real environment tested:** Linux 4.19.112, Node.js via tsx, openclaw workspace importing the production `scanEmptyAllowlistPolicyWarnings` module with vitest mocks for `getDoctorChannelCapabilities`.\\n\\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\\n```\\n$ pnpm vitest run src/commands/doctor/shared/empty-allowlist-scan.test.ts --reporter=verbose\\n\\n \\u2713 doctor empty allowlist policy scan > scans top-level and account-scoped channel warnings\\n \\u2713 doctor empty allowlist policy scan > allows provider-specific extra warnings without importing providers\\n \\u2713 doctor empty allowlist policy scan > does not warn about parent groupAllowFrom when every account overrides it\\n \\u2713 doctor empty allowlist policy scan > still warns about parent groupAllowFrom when some accounts lack it\\n \\u2713 doctor empty allowlist policy scan > suppresses parent warning when all accounts have allowFrom with fallback enabled\\n \\u2713 doctor empty allowlist policy scan > does not suppress parent warning when accounts have allowFrom but fallback is disabled\\n \\u2713 doctor empty allowlist policy scan > suppresses parent warning when enabled accounts override and disabled account does not\\n \\u2713 doctor empty allowlist policy scan > skips disabled channel and account entries\\n\\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\\n      Tests  8 passed (8)\\n```\\n\\n**Evidence after fix:**\\n\\n| Scenario | Expected | Result |\\n|----------|----------|--------|\\n| Empty parent + all accounts override with `groupAllowFrom` | No warning | \\u2705 |\\n| Empty parent + some accounts lack `groupAllowFrom` | Parent warning | \\u2705 |\\n| Empty parent + all accounts use `allowFrom` (fallback-capable channel) | No warning | \\u2705 |\\n| Empty parent + accounts use `allowFrom` (non-fallback channel) | Parent warning | \\u2705 |\\n| Enabled accounts override + disabled account lacks allowlist | No warning | \\u2705 |\\n| DM policy warnings at parent scope | Preserved | \\u2705 |\\n\\n**Observed result after fix:** Parent-level group-allowlist warning is suppressed when every enabled child account carries its own populated effective group sender allowlist (either explicit `groupAllowFrom` or `allowFrom` on fallback-capable channels). DM-policy warnings at the parent scope continue to fire. When even one enabled account lacks its own list, the parent warning is preserved.\\n\\n**What was not tested:** Integration with specific channel plugins (signal, telegram, discord, etc.). The fix operates at the shared `scanEmptyAllowlistPolicyWarnings` layer before plugin-specific hooks fire, so it applies uniformly.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm vitest run src/commands/doctor/shared/empty-allowlist-scan.test.ts` \\u2014 8 passed\\n- [x] `pnpm vitest run src/commands/doctor/shared/empty-allowlist-policy.test.ts` \\u2014 4 passed\\n- [x] Regression: empty parent + all accounts override `groupAllowFrom` \\u2192 no warning\\n- [x] Regression: empty parent + all accounts use `allowFrom` with fallback \\u2192 no warning\\n- [x] Regression: empty parent + disabled account lacking allowlist \\u2192 no warning\\n- [x] Regression: empty parent + non-fallback channel with `allowFrom` \\u2192 warning preserved\\n- [x] Regression: some accounts lack \\u2192 warning preserved\\n- [x] Regression: DM warnings preserved at parent scope\\n\"",
        "branch": "fix/issue-92684-doctor-empty-allowlist",
